race.comment: EL TORO MACHO (2) kept safe in betting on debut from the wide gate when a battling third over 1250m at Newcastle. Further improved now with that run and can stalk the speed from the inside gate. Ready to win. EVERYBODY RISE (1) has a fitness edge over most of these fourth-up and far from disgraced at latest when a tiring fifth over 1200m at Kembla Grange. Cross-over nose band comes off, and he gets a key jockey change. SHE SWINGS (4) was in need of the run first-up after the one trial when a plugging fifth over 1100m at Goulburn. Comes to hand quickly and shouldn't be a maiden for long. VANTABLACK (8) unwanted in betting on resumption ($21), when a solid fourth over 1200m at Kembla Grange. Likely improver from the good gate.
